This screen shows the p5.js Web Editor interface with a code editor on the left and a preview pane on the right.

**Code (JavaScript):**
```javascript
let cities;

function preload() {
  cities = loadJSON('assets/cities.json');
}

function setup() {
  createCanvas(400, 400);
  console.log(cities);
}

function draw() {
  background(220);
}
```

**Visual output:** The preview pane shows a solid light gray square (the canvas) against a white background.

**UI state:** The editor is open to the file `sketch.js`. A sidebar on the left shows a file structure containing `index.html`, `sketch.js`, and `style.css`. The top of the browser shows several open tabs, including "p5.js Web Editor | maps e..." and "1000 Largest US Cities B...".

The image shows the p5.js Web Editor interface with a JavaScript file named `sketch.js` open in the editor pane.

